The article discusses the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. and emphasizes the importance of taking action to uphold his ideals of justice, equality, and opportunity. It highlights the need to protect the right to vote, confront racism and white supremacy, and strive for economic justice. The article calls for federal legislation to address voter suppression and election subversion and urges Americans to engage in civic, community, and service projects in honor of Dr. King. President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaims Monday, January 17, 2022, as the Martin Luther King, Jr., Federal Holiday and encourages Americans to visit www.MLKDay.gov to find service projects across the country.